xxl.core.functions

Class CMDFunction<P,R,I,M>

  • java.lang.Object
    • xxl.core.functions.DecoratorFunction<P,R>
      • xxl.core.functions.FunctionMetaDataFunction<P,R,CompositeMetaData<I,M>>
        • xxl.core.functions.CMDFunction<P,R,I,M>
  • Type Parameters:
    P - the type of the function's parameters.
    R - the return type of the function.
    I - the type of the identifiers used by the composite meta data.
    M - the type of the metadata fragments used by the composite meta data.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Function<P,R>, MetaDataFunction<P,R,CompositeMetaData<I,M>>, Decorator<Function<? super P,? extends R>>, MetaDataProvider<CompositeMetaData<I,M>>

    public class CMDFunction<P,R,I,M>
extends FunctionMetaDataFunction<P,R,CompositeMetaData<I,M>>
    This class provides a CMDFunction (= CompositeMetaDataFunction). It is an implementation of MetaDataFunction that uses a hash map to store the meta data.
